## DOCKERFILE REQUIREMENTS
ENV ENABLE_WEB_INTERFACE=true must be present.
Dockerfile must be at project root.

## INFERENCE SCRIPT REQUIREMENTS
Must use HF router base URL, not api.openai.com.
API key loaded from HF_TOKEN environment variable only.
Model: Qwen/Qwen2.5-72B-Instruct (or similar via HF router).
Must run end-to-end with: uv run inference.py
Reward values logged per episode — must show diversity across runs.

## CODE QUALITY RULES
- Type hints on every function signature.
- No bare except clauses.
- No print debugging left in final files.
- Every method that touches state must be called only after reset().
- _grade() and _process_score() are private methods, never called externally.
- get_state() returns a copy or the live ModGuardState — never None.

## WHEN GENERATING CODE
1. Read the relevant existing file first before writing or editing.
2. Write complete files — no "rest remains the same" placeholders.
3. After writing, state explicitly which spec rules each section satisfies.
4. If a test fails, paste the full traceback before attempting a fix.
5. Never fix a bug by relaxing a spec constraint.

## KNOWN BUGS TO FIX (from audit)
1. escalation_budget underflow: when budget_violated=True, do not decrement
   escalation_budget. Add guard before the decrement line.
2. hard mode ai_confidence_score: remove the 70/30 probability split.
   Use pure inversion: score = 1.0 - base, always.